4. Baked Sweet Potatoes and Chicken

• Ingredients: Chicken breast, sweet potatoes, olive oil, salt, pepper, your favorite seasoning.
• Prep Tip: Bake sweet potatoes and chicken on a sheet tray, seasoning both. Bake together in the oven and store in the fridge. Just reheat when ready to eat.

5. Egg Muffins

• Ingredients: Eggs, spinach, mushrooms, bell peppers, salt, and pepper.
• Prep Tip: Whisk the eggs and mix with chopped vegetables. Pour into muffin tins and bake. You can prepare several for the week, and they’re easy to grab and go.

6. Pasta with Lentils and Tomato Sauce

• Ingredients: Whole-grain pasta, lentils, tomato sauce, garlic, and onions.
• Prep Tip: Make a large batch of lentils with tomato sauce and cook the pasta in bulk. Store them together and reheat before serving.

7. Overnight Oats

• Ingredients: Rolled oats, milk (or plant-based milk), chia seeds (1 tbs), honey, and fresh fruit.
• Prep Tip: The night before, mix oats, milk, and chia seeds in jars. Let it sit overnight, then add fresh fruit in the morning for a quick, balanced breakfast.

8. Grilled Salmon with Quinoa and Veggies

• Ingredients: Salmon fillets, quinoa, mixed vegetables (steamed or roasted), olive oil, lemon.
• Prep Tip: Grill or bake salmon, cook quinoa, and steam veggies in bulk. Store in separate containers for an easy meal.

9. Rice and Beans

• Ingredients: Brown rice, black beans, corn, salsa, avocado, lime juice.
• Prep Tip: Cook rice and beans in bulk and keep in separate containers. Mix together when ready to eat, adding salsa, corn, avocado, and lime juice for extra flavor.<|user|>